Kyoto International Conference Center, designed by Sachio Otani (1966), was the location of the historic 1997 &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kyoto_Protocol&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Kyoto Protocol Treaty&lt;/a&gt; that brought climate change to international attention, committing countries to reduce greenhouse gas emissions.

&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
国立京都国際会館は、大谷幸夫の設計（1966年）で、気候変動が国際的に注目され、各国が温室効果ガスの排出を削減することを約束した歴史的な1997年の&lt;a href=&quot;https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/気候変動に関する国際連合枠組条約の京都議定書&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;京都議定書条約&lt;/a&gt;の締結場所である。
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Architecture" /><category term="Black and White" /><summary type="html">Kyoto International Conference Center, designed by Sachio Otani (1966), was the location of the historic 1997 Kyoto Protocol Treaty that brought climate change to international attention, committing countries to reduce greenhouse gas emissions.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2023/2303_DSCF7291-2.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2023/2303_DSCF7291-2.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Jonangu・城南宮</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/230311/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Jonangu・城南宮" /><published>2023-03-11T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2023-03-11T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/jonangu</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/230311/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
